ClientSession.targetLatencyNanos: 80ms → 25ms. Now that AudioPlayer.schedule queues buffers back-to-back via the engine's own queue (only the FIRST buffer is hostTime-anchored), per-packet jitter headroom is no longer needed. 25ms is below the 50ms echo-perception threshold so the host's local audio and the client's playback in the same room sound like a single source instead of a doubled-up echo, which is what the user just reported.